Description of incident: Information on this security breach is provided by the Office of the California Attorney General. ** Disclaimer: ** The number of breached records reported reflects our best estimate, based on all the data currently available, surrounding this breach. Because the specific number of breached records was not disclosed in the notification letter sent to the California Attorney General?s Office, the number is estimated as the minimum number of breached records necessary to trigger the obligation of notification to the Attorney General under California statute. Under Cal. Civ. Code 1798.29, 1798.82, notification to the Attorney General is only required whenever a breach of records affects more than 500 California residents. If you believe this number is inaccurate, please contact us at chronology@privacyrights.org
